[This notification to the OIE officially confirms the report published in ProMED postings 20150828.3608767 and 20150905.3626182. However, the OIE report does generate additional questions. While the report mentions that the source of infection was due to the entry of live animals, it is not clear when such animals became infected, especially given that the animals were coming from a country where the disease has never been reported. These horses may very well have been in contact with horses from other areas where the disease may occur. The characterization of the serotype will be of great value for determining the origin of the infection.

There is mention of unofficial information (see report below) noting over 100 infected animals. So, it would be useful to know the total number of affected cases, and not only the number of initial cases.

As ProMED-mail moderator AS commented in posting 20150905.3626182, the source of infection needs to be clarified. We now have confirmation of the infection, so determining and clarifying the source would be helpful.

For further information and spread of the disease in Malaysia, subscribers are referred to Mod.TG's and Mod.AS's recent commentaries in postings 20150828.3608767 and 20150905.3626182. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3629570,147.]
